==English==

===Etymology===
Acronym of 'laughing out loud' or 'lot of laughs'

===Pronunciation===
* IPA: /&#603;l-o&#650;-&#603;l/, /l&#593;l/, or /lo&#650;l/

===Interjection===
'''lol''' 

#{{txt}} used to express [[laughter]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: '''lol''', *[[naur]]*
*French: '''lol''', [[mdr]]
*Hungarian: '''lol''', '''hfn''' ('hangosan felnevet')
*Italian: '''lol''' ('ridere molto/forte')
*Japanese: [[w]], [[ワラ]] (wara)
*Spanish: '''reva''' ('reiéndose en voz alta')

===Usage note===
"lol" is an internet shorthand ([[jargon]]) hence it was originally almost never used in speech, however in many online video games users are increasingly using this word instead of laughter.  It may also be used jokingly or sarcastically in speech.

